race.comment: WILL IT SNOW (4) is an improver in the Laming yard who missed a whisker over this trip at Ipswich. Maps well enough and won't have to improve much to take this out. MAKAMAE (12) found the line nicely last start when narrowly beaten over 1800m at this track. Had one here prior over longer, and this is winnable with average luck from an outside barrier. PIERONIMO (6) peaks for the Archibald yard and he got too far back this track/trip last time. He is still short of his best and is capable of settling closer  SACRED BULL (2) was tracking well before a plainer run placing at Ipswich last time. Has an awkward gate but is good enough to consider. GOOD PHILLY (5) would be around the mark if she puts her best foot forward.
